      <h1>Built form, condition &amp; valuation</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The physical-building cluster — how the property is built, what
        condition it's in, what's fixed to it, what surveyors say about it,
        and what it's worth. Five sub-pages by object sub-cluster.
      </p>

      <aside class="callout callout--key" role="note">
        <p class="callout__label">The shape of this cluster</p>
        <p>
          Built form is the structural description; condition is what's
          gone wrong or been altered; fixtures &amp; fittings is the
          schedule of what travels with the sale; surveys are the
          professional assessments; valuation is the agreed money.
          The shared lifecycle is <em>inspection → report → settlement</em>.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <h2 id="subpages">Pages in this cluster</h2>
      <ul class="cluster-index">
        <li><a href="/schema/built-form/built-form-form"><strong>Built form</strong></a> — construction, year, type, parking, smart-home systems, summary &amp; media.</li>
        <li><a href="/schema/built-form/condition"><strong>Condition</strong></a> — alterations, electrical works, defects, declared condition.</li>
        <li><a href="/schema/built-form/fixtures"><strong>Fixtures &amp; fittings</strong></a> — full TA10 schedule by room: items to include / remove, kitchen, bathroom, carpets, curtains, lights, outdoor, services.</li>
        <li><a href="/schema/built-form/surveys"><strong>Surveys</strong></a> — RICS Home Survey structure: grounds, inside (roof / floors / finishes), outside (chimneys / envelope / extras), services, legal, valuation block, advice &amp; risks.</li>
        <li><a href="/schema/built-form/valuation"><strong>Valuation</strong></a> — valuations and price information.</li>
      </ul>
</Layout>
